INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2012-05-06 19:54:20','2012-05-06 19:54:20','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','trash','open','open','','hello-world','','','2012-05-15 02:49:53','2012-05-15 02:49:53','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2012-05-06 19:54:20','2012-05-06 19:54:20','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://localhost:8080/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','trash','open','open','','sample-page','','','2012-05-06 21:03:51','2012-05-06 21:03:51','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(318,1,'2012-05-26 01:17:19','2012-05-26 05:17:19','<div class=\"column copy\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?attachment_id=298\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-298\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-298\" title=\"about_icon\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/about_icon2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"29\" height=\"31\" /></a>Let\'s talk.</h3>\r\nIdeas in flux, hikes in the woods, and exchanging tips on making things? I\'m listening... If you\'d like to chat, look all the way to the right and you will find some relevant contact info. If you\'d like to work on a project with me, send your timeline and budget along with the breif too!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"column blog\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?attachment_id=299\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-299\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-299\" title=\"blog_icon\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/blog_icon1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"29\" /></a> From my blog</h3>\r\nI snap pictures and sometimes write thoughts. You can read them here!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"column contact\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?attachment_id=300\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-300\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-300\" title=\"contact_icon\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/contact_icon1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"29\" height=\"22\" /></a>Contact</h3>\r\nTweets: @micahspear\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEmail me: micah[at]playtimecollective.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\niChat: micahrobinspear\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>','x','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-32','','','2012-05-26 01:17:19','2012-05-26 05:17:19','',10,'http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=318',0,'revision','',0),(4,1,'2012-05-06 20:53:08','2012-05-06 20:53:08','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-229\" title=\"hoeweler_micah_final21-731x1024\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/hoeweler_micah_final21-731x1024-214x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"214\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nPlayfulness and improvisation are vital organs in the body of my design process. I love creating winning products, and because some of the most remarkable inventions were an accident, it excites me to experiment with my ideas. I grew up in the countryside where I climbed trees and played in the woods. From a young age I was blowing glass, painting canvases, shooting travel photography, and making things. I’ve put these passions to work at Art School, Design School, and Business School where I focused on Service Design and Environmental Studies.\r\n\r\nI’ve experimented with different strategies of identifying and realizing scalable and high impact products on my own and in teams working closely with others. I’ve consulted for <strong>Louis Vuitton</strong> on luxury marketing strategy and service design, <strong>Memorial Sloan Kettering</strong> on Health Service Innovation for chemotherapy patients and <strong>First Niagara Bank</strong> on Gen-Y strategy. I’ve recently consulted with <strong>MTV </strong>and was a panelist invited by <strong>WHATIF</strong> for a study on Gen-Y trends. I have traveled the world extensively (my passport is almost full), I’m a pro at Where’s Waldo and I can be very competitive on the foose-ball table!\r\n\r\nEducation: Maryland Institute College of Art, Yestermerrow Design Build School, Eugene Lang the New School for Liberal Arts, Parsons the New School for Design, Columbia Business School\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;','About','','publish','open','open','','projects','','','2012-05-26 11:59:33','2012-05-26 15:59:33','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?page_id=4',0,'page','',0),(5,1,'2012-05-06 20:52:59','2012-05-06 20:52:59','','Projects','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision','','','2012-05-06 20:52:59','2012-05-06 20:52:59','',4,'http://localhost:8080/?p=5',0,'revision','',0),(6,1,'2012-05-26 11:55:57','2012-05-26 15:55:57','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-229\" title=\"hoeweler_micah_final21-731x1024\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/hoeweler_micah_final21-731x1024-214x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"214\" height=\"300\" />\n\nPlayfulness and improvisation are vital organs in the body of my design process. I love creating winning products, and because some of the most remarkable inventions were an accident, it excites me to experiment with my ideas. I grew up in the countryside where I climbed trees and played in the woods. From a young age I was blowing glass, painting canvases, shooting travel photography, and making things. I’ve put these passions to work at Art School, Design School, and Business School where I focused on Service Design and Environmental Studies.\n\nI’ve experimented with different strategies of identifying and realizing scalable and high impact products on my own and in teams working closely with others. I’ve consulted for <strong>Louis Vuitton</strong> on luxury marketing strategy and service design, <strong>Memorial Sloan Kettering</strong> on Health Service Innovation for chemotherapy patients and <strong>First Niagara Bank</strong> on Gen-Y strategy. I’ve recently consulted with <strong>MTV </strong>and was a panelist invited by <strong>WHATIF</strong> for a study on Gen-Y trends. I have traveled the world extensively (my passport is almost full), I’m a pro at Where’s Waldo and I can be very competitive on the foose-ball table!\n<div>Education: Maryland Institute College of Art, Yestermerrow Design Build School, Eugene Lang the New School for Liberal Arts, Parsons the New School for Design, Columbia Business School</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n&nbsp;\n<div></div>\n&nbsp;','About','','inherit','open','open','','4-autosave','','','2012-05-26 11:55:57','2012-05-26 15:55:57','',4,'http://localhost:8080/?p=6',0,'revision','',0),(70,1,'2012-05-10 04:47:45','2012-05-10 04:47:45','<strong>@micahspear:</strong>\r\n\r\n[twitter username=micahspear]\r\n\r\n[skills]\r\n\r\n[skill value=\"100\" color=\"red\" text=\"Photoshop\"]\r\n\r\n[skill value=\"80\" color=\"yellow\" text=\"Illustrator\"]\r\n\r\n[skill value=\"90\" color=\"blue\" text=\"HTML/CSS\"]\r\n\r\n[skill value=\"65\" color=\"gray\" text=\"JavaScript\"]\r\n\r\n[skill value=\"45\" color=\"green\" text=\"WordPress\"]\r\n\r\n[skill value=\"35\" color=\"brown\" text=\"PHP/mySQL\"]\r\n\r\n[/skills]\r\n\r\nwhoa, this skills thing is weird and cool.','About','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-9','','','2012-05-10 04:47:45','2012-05-10 04:47:45','',4,'http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=70',0,'revision','',0),(7,1,'2012-05-06 20:53:08','2012-05-06 20:53:08','This is some text.','Projects','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-2','','','2012-05-06 20:53:08','2012-05-06 20:53:08','',4,'http://localhost:8080/?p=7',0,'revision','',0),(8,1,'2012-05-06 21:02:51','2012-05-06 21:02:51','<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"serv_icons\">\r\n<div class=\"grid_4\">\r\n<div class=\"serv_icon1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?attachment_id=333\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-333\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-333\" title=\"playtimeicon-03\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/playtimeicon-033.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"125\" height=\"126\" /></a><a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/icons-021.png\">\r\n</a></div>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Insight</h3>\r\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"left\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nHow do you identify an “aha moment”? Think about it for a second. Finding design gaps and revealing opportunities can appear out of thin air. It takes keen awareness and a finely tuned listening to realize the hidden nature of things. Ask questions first, design later. That\'s how I do it.\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"grid_4\">\r\n<div class=\"serv_icon2\"></div>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?attachment_id=334\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-334\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-334\" title=\"playtimeicon-02\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/playtimeicon-022.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"125\" height=\"126\" /></a>Innovation</h3>\r\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"left\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nEffective, innovative ideas take disruptive thinking and resourceful intuition; combine these assets with an understanding and appreciation of our social and technological evolution. The result is that thoughtful leveraging of such perception with knowledge of what’s possible can produce winning products.<span style=\"text-align: center;\"> </span>\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"grid_4\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?attachment_id=337\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-337\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-337\" title=\"playtimeicon-01\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/playtimeicon-012.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"125\" height=\"126\" /></a>Direction</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For me building products and creating in teams is all about the back and force conversation of what\'s possible. I\'m excited to produce products that can be celebrated - and that takes a capable comunicative team. I curate and empower designers and project managers to push through creative boundaries with tight timelines. We do it well and have fun too. Direction is about leading the way, together.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"grid_4\">\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?attachment_id=336\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-336\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-336\" title=\"playtimeicon-04\" src=\"http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/playtimeicon-043.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"125\" height=\"126\" /></a>Playt