g\" alt=\"\" width=\"214\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nPlayfulness and improvisation are vital organs in the body of my design process. I love producing winning products, and because some of the most remarkable inventions were created by accident, this excites me to experiment with my ideas. I intend on bringing design and technology closer, thoughtfully. From a young age I was blowing glass, painting canvases, shooting travel photography, and making things. I\'ve put these passions to work at Art School, Design School, and Business School where I focused on Service Design and Environmental Studies. I’ve experimented with different strategies of identifying and realizing scalable and high impact products individually and in teams of all types. Recently I’ve consulted for <strong>Louis Vuitton</strong> on luxury marketing strategy and service design, <strong>Memorial Sloan Kettering</strong> on Health Service Innovation for chemo therapy patients, <strong>First Niagara Bank</strong> on Gen-Y strategy, and was recently <strong>MTV </strong>and a panelist invited by <strong>WHATIF</strong> for a study on Gen-Y trends. I grew up in the country side where I climbed trees and played in the woods. My passport is almost full. I’m a pro at Where’s Waldo, I get competitive on the foose-ball table – and like a good challenge!\r\n<div style=\"float: right; width: 35%; clear: right;\">\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Education: Maryland Institute College of Art, Eugene Lang The New School for Liberal Arts, Parsons The New School for Design, Columbia Business School</p>\r\n[twitter username=micahspear]','About','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-53','','','2012-05-16 15:14:41','2012-05-16 15:14:41','',4,'http://ec2-50-17-60-123.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=248',0,'revision','',0),(211,1,'2012-05-13 16:16:39','2012-05-13 16:16:39','<div class=\"clear\" style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"serv_icons\">\r\n<div class=\"grid_4\">\r\n